<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ensure that you meet the level requirements. Exceptions may be made if there are any shortages of classes.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Understand that raids are not intended for experience. They are intended to achieve a common goal such as attaining an epic piece, getting particular gear that will upgrade our raid force, and even teaching others how to raid or how to lead a raid. <br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ensure that you have posted your intent to participate on the guild message board at least 2 days BEFORE the event. <br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Research the zone and mobs in the zone as well as the boss mob. <br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Print a map of the zone. <br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Read the raid posting for any special notes on tactics, CR plans, etc.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp BE ON TIME and at the meeting location. This is imperative! If at all possible be 15 minutes early.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Have all your essential reagents, weapons, resist gear, and stuff with you. <br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The guild bank will provide the reagents for the raid as we have started to collect money from the mini raids that we done. These reagents are to be used for raids only and any left over should be returned to the guild bank.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Please make sure that you have enough time to participate! If you don’t let the raid leader know well in advance so that he/she can locate a replacement. If a RL situation comes up have a gate potion on you so that the raid will not be interrupted.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Try to have pop, beer, and munchies ready to limit the amount of AFK’s.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Be prepared to test the limits of your patience. Raids take time and since we are relatively new some things may take longer than usual. <br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Make sure all settings are correct; if performance is a problem turn off 3D sky, particle effects, luclin models, and dynamic lighting. Dying due to a miss cast on a heal is very annoying.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Turn off battle spam. You do not need to see others hits, misses, you misses, peoples spell casting and so forth.<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Prepare all hotkeys that you will need prior to the raid.<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Set up buff spells that will be needed during the initial buffing session.<br>
<br>
·&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Last but not least be patient. <br>
